Meet <b>Shenee</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Shenee lives at <a href='/home/?user=fling_frog100'>58618 Panther Road</a> in one of Westridge's most stylish and modern homes.  She says that she chose the house for its wonderful views of Millsberry, which have been inspiring her since she moved in on October 30, 2005.<br><br>One of Shenee's best qualities is her friendliness.  She is extremely outgoing and can start up a pleasant conversation with even the grumpiest person!  Shenee has already built a wide and varied circle of friends.  Because she has such a flexible personality, Shenee is equally happy spending an afternoon playing in her tree house, hanging out at an ice cream parlor, or visiting a mall to check out the latest orange, zebra-stripe, and pink fashions.  She's willing to try new things and go to new places, if it'll make her friends happy.  Shenee is most definitely a people person!<br><br>In addition to her varied group of friends, Shenee has very diverse interests.  She loves spending dark, stormy nights curled up with a good mystery book.  Shenee says that she likes the challenge of figuring out "whodunnit?" before reaching the end of a book.  She hopes to someday write her own mystery novel and has revealed that she plans to write the ending first and work her way backward.  Shenee is a fan of mystery in general, however, because she also loves magic tricks!  She likes learning the intricacies of a trick and takes pride in being able to make her audience believe that she has really performed the impossible.<br><br>Shenee's favorite hobby, though, is music.  She's very expressive and loves to practice her singing in front a mirror, so she can really hone her performance.  Shenee's favorite kinds of music are pop, punk, and heavy metal, and she hopes to combine aspects of all three in her very own unique style!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Shenee, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
